Tri-Star Pictures Inc said it wonpermanent relief from various provisions of the 1952 ConsentJudgment and 1980 Order that apply to the Loews' TheatreCircuit, which Tri-Star acquired last December.    It said the U.S. District Court for the Southern Districtof New York agreed to permit exhibition of Tri-Star motionpictures in loews theaters and to allow Tri-Star to conduct itsbusiness other than with Loews free from restructions of thecourt's earlier orders. Reuter&#3;